Reading about Core Transformations. Changing your motivation scheme which uses negative emotion to push you towards action. It proses just removing the negative-emotion-as-motivator completely, and that when you do so, it doesn’t remove your values or wants to take action, and you actually become more effective. 

I definitely feel trapped in that. I’ll often get stuck in loops where I “feel bad but can’t stop until I’ve done work X”. In this framework, fixing the feeling directly should be step one. After that work on X will be much easier (or you may realize you should work on Y). 

This feels connected to the talk about working at Tesla from earlier today. Musk is always working on the top bottleneck. Once is fixed, he jumps to the next one. He singularly focuses on the bottlenecks. 

That’s easy to say, but I find in practice it’s difficult in one’s life to identify what the bottlenecks are. But for me, maybe it’s this negative motivation scheme is it? Maybe focusing / CT is the solution? Quitting my job didn’t reduce the negative feelings as much as I would’ve hoped. Now I was just getting them from self-imposed goals and judgements instead of externally.

A pattern: I forget something. I wish I hadn’t / didn’t. I feel bad for having forgotten / not having built systems to avoid situations like this. Feel I need to work harder to fix things so I don’t end up feeling bad again. Know that I’m not gonna remember to stay resolved to fix it. Bad feels intensify. Fixing problem now feels even more important. Bad feels intensify again. Etc
